  "prompt": "I am an average student preparing for the IIT-JEE. Which test series is the best for me for free?",
  "response": "As an average student preparing for the IIT-JEE, there are several free test series options you can consider to help you practice and gauge your understanding. Here are some popular ones:\n\n1. **Unacademy**: Unacademy often provides free test series for IIT-JEE aspirants. You can register on their platform and access various tests.\n\n2. **Vedantu**: Vedantu offers a free JEE test series which includes multiple mock tests based on the JEE pattern. Signing up on their platform should give you access.\n\n3. **Embibe**: Embibe has a wealth of resources, including free test series and practice questions for IIT-JEE aspirants. Their analytics can help you identify areas to improve.\n\n4. **Toppr**: Toppr offers a few free mock tests for JEE aspirants. You can sign up and access their test series which can help in your preparation.\n\n5. **NTA (National Testing Agency)**: The NTA provides sample papers and previous years' question papers, which can be useful for self-assessment.\n\n6. **ALLEN Career Institute**: They provide various resources, including free test series. Check their website for more information.\n\n7. **Aakash BYJU'S**: They sometimes offer free mock tests for JEE aspirants. You can visit their site to see current offerings.\n\nBefore choosing a test series, make sure to check the level of difficulty and the alignment with your current study materials. Consistently practicing through these test series can greatly enhance your preparation for IIT-JEE. Good luck!",
